
set git username email in woindows

To set your Git username and email on Windows (using Git Bash or Command Prompt), use these commands:

🔹 Set globally (recommended)
This will apply to all your repositories:

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
🔹 Set for a specific repository only
Run these inside your project folder:

git config user.name "Your Name"
git config user.email "your@email.com"
🔹 Check your current config
To verify:

git config --global user.name
git config --global user.email
Or see everything:

git config --list
🔹 If you need to change GitHub account (important ⚠️)
If you're getting a 403 permission error, it's usually not just username/email—you need to update authentication:

Option 1: Use Personal Access Token (PAT)
Go to GitHub

Generate a Personal Access Token

Use it instead of password when pushing

Option 2: Clear saved credentials (Windows)
Run:

git credential-manager reject https://github.com
Or manually:

Open Control Panel

Go to Credential Manager

Remove saved GitHub credentials

Option 3: Use SSH (best long-term)
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"
Then add the key to GitHub

