That message is completely normal 👍 — it just means:

You are on branch main

Your local repo is already synced with remote (origin/main)

There are no new changes to commit

🔍 What it implies
nothing to commit, working tree clean
➡️ No modified / new / deleted files
➡️ Git has nothing to push

🔹 If you expected changes but don’t see them
1. Check file status
git status
2. Make sure files are saved
Sometimes editors don’t save automatically.

3. Add and commit changes
If you made changes:

git add .
git commit -m "your message"
git push
🔹 If your goal was related to contributors issue
This message also tells us:

👉 You haven’t changed commit history yet, so:

Old contributors will still appear on GitHub

To remove them, you must:

Rewrite history OR

Create a fresh repo

🔹 Quick check (important)
Run this to confirm whose commits exist:

git log --pretty=format:"%an <%ae>"
If you still see the old user → that’s why they show as contributor.

